What insurance is appropriate for me?
Insurance for a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense that depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to figure out what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This undertaking takes the form of an insurance contract stipulating that the insurance company will receive an agreed insured amount of a certain amount for taking responsibility for paying the damages in the event of an insurance claim.
The insurance premium is the cost of the insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of the driving licence, the type of vehicle that is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the more likely an accident is to be, the higher the premium rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and the women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies concluded that people living in a marriage tend to have fewer crashes than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the journeys and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The rise in the frequency of the journeys increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies are considering when setting the cost of premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well to choose the kind of insurance that best matches his policyholder's profile.
We will show the most important variables here for the selection of this type of insurance, which, in addition to the fact that they comply with the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 experience different drawbacks, such as little experience driving and short possession of a driving licence when they want to take out premiums at an affordable price.
While insuring against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most consumers can choose insurance against all risks with premiums discount to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would presuppose a client's contribution to the reimbursement of the insured event.
"Part of the reimbursement of the insurance claim provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premiums, which will be the higher, which would be the lower, the co-payment," explains Luis Noguera, the senior head of First Europe in Spain, an internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other operators by the client insuring against the damage caused to other persons, but not against the damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as possible, as this will affect your bonus and make it possible to reduce your premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate held by the insurance company.
By contrast, malus is an increase in that basic rate.
"The revolution and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year mark, it is easier for drivers to take out insurance, as the client's risk index is reduced, thanks to their acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience of the pre-existence when the accident is made, nor in the driving process," assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of proceedings, when the "fear of a newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to take out insurance against all risks, if his economic situation permits.
Families with children are considered by insurers to be clients with the lowest risk-reality index and thus their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks at a discount of premiums (which could be €300) or a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their proceedings are calmer and their purchaseability is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to have insurance against all risks at a premium discount (which is €150) or insurance extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It has to be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of a crash, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a valid reason for the appropriate insuring of the insurance options that would suit us best in view of our personal situation.
